  "prompt": "What is meant by the hindi term 'bakchodi'?",
  "response": "The Hindi term \"bakchodi\" (\u092c\u0915\u091a\u094b\u0926\u0940) is a colloquial expression that refers to talking nonsense, engaging in frivolous or silly conversation, or making meaningless remarks. It's often used informally to describe situations where people are joking around, bantering, or wasting time on trivial matters. The term can carry a light-hearted or humorous connotation, though it may also imply annoyance if someone feels that the conversation is unproductive or pointless.",
